        <abstract> 
<p>Congratulates THH on first number of <hi rend="italic">Natural History Review</hi>.</p>  
<p>THH’s article on brain ["On the zoological relations of man with the lower animals", <hi rend="italic">Nat. Hist. Rev.</hi> (1861): 67–84] completely smashes Owen.</p>  
<p>Owen’s Leeds address [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> (1858): xlix–cx].</p> 
            <p>In his historical sketch of opinion on species CD has picked out some sentences [by Owen] with which he will take some revenge. CD is not bold enough to come to an open quarrel.</p>
        </abstract>
